#: src/pages/docs/concepts/TimingSyncPage.tsx:53
msgid "Genlock is the broadcast practice of locking every device's frame timing to one shared reference signal — historically an analog \"black burst\" or tri-level sync feed distributed around the facility. When everything is genlocked, every camera and every output starts its frames at the same instant, so video can be switched and mixed without glitches or re-buffering."
msgstr "Genlock is the broadcast practice of locking every device's frame timing to one shared reference signal — historically an analog \"black burst\" or tri-level sync feed distributed around the facility. When everything is genlocked, every camera and every output starts its frames at the same instant, so video can be switched and mixed without glitches or re-buffering."

