#: src/pages/docs/concepts/GlossaryPage.tsx:148
msgid "The MPEG transport stream container used throughout broadcast: fixed 188-byte packets multiplexing video, audio, subtitles, and data on numbered PIDs, designed to stay decodable through noise and joins. Carried over UDP/multicast in facilities and inside SRT across the internet."
msgstr "The MPEG transport stream container used throughout broadcast: fixed 188-byte packets multiplexing video, audio, subtitles, and data on numbered PIDs, designed to stay decodable through noise and joins. Carried over UDP/multicast in facilities and inside SRT across the internet."

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/TransportsPage.tsx:175
msgid "The MPEG transport stream is the container broadcast infrastructure speaks: a self-synchronizing packet format that multiplexes video, audio, subtitles, and data on numbered PIDs. Sent over UDP — usually to a multicast group so one sender feeds any number of receivers on the network — it is the classic in-facility distribution method, with latency well under a second."
msgstr "The MPEG transport stream is the container broadcast infrastructure speaks: a self-synchronizing packet format that multiplexes video, audio, subtitles, and data on numbered PIDs. Sent over UDP — usually to a multicast group so one sender feeds any number of receivers on the network — it is the classic in-facility distribution method, with latency well under a second."

